item.title: Back To School Outfit, Hair, and Drugstore Makeup Tutorial!
item.description:
Back To School Outfit, Hair, and Drugstore Makeup Tutorial!
FOLLOW ME ON TWITTER! http://www.twitter.com/juicystar007 This tutorial is targeted towards the high school age range. But of course, if you like it-- do it! No matter the age! Outfit: loose V-neck (mine is from american eagle) long scarf (mine is from H&M)--remember, plaid and metallics are IN this fall! bangles (mine are from H&M) jeans coach pop c tote (from the new poppy collection!) Hair: While your hair is damp at night, braid it into 2-4 different braids, spray with hair spray. sleep. wake up! blow dry while still in braids on hot, spray again. take out! spray and scrunch. have beautiful mermaid hair!! If you shower in the morning-- wet your hair at night, braid it into 2-4 different braids, spray with hair spray. sleep. wake up! in the morning keep your hair in the braids and put them into a shower cap. shower (you do not need to blow dry the hair because the heat from the shower will do the trick!) get out of the shower, spray braids, take braids out. spray and scrunch. have beautiful mermaid hair!! Makeup: FACE- your normal makeup face routine! almay smart shader blush in #010 pink/rose EYES- primer- (i used cliche cosmetics eye primer bought here: http://www.clichecosmetics.com ) but would have used loreal decrease eye primer if i had it. physicians formula shimmer strip in vegas strip black shadow nyx white eye liner loreal paris lineur intense felt tip eyeliner in carbon black maybelline pulse perfection mascara in very black LIPS: cover girl outlast double lipshine in 200 BRUSHES: loew-cornelle maxines mop brush in 3/8 inch (bought from michael's craft store) MAC DUPE: 239 sonia kashuk large crease brush (bought at target) MAC DUPE: 224 pencil brush (bought at http://www.coastalscents.com) MAC DUPE: 219
